sentences.sContent: To the untrue man, the whole universe is false- it is impalpable- it shrinks to nothing within his grasp.
sentences.sContent_eng: To the untrue man, the whole universe is false- it is impalpable- it shrinks to nothing within his grasp.
sentences.sCn: 对那个不真实的人来说，整个宇宙都是虚伪的——都是难以触摸的，在他的把握之中化为子虚乌有。

sentences.sContent: With the development of breast screening, more cancers are detected in the very early impalpable phase.
sentences.sContent_eng: With the development of breast screening, more cancers are detected in the very early impalpable phase.
sentences.sCn: 通过乳房筛查的普及，更多癌症在早期甚至难以被触摸到的时候就被发现。

synos.tran: 感触不到的；难理解的；无形的

remMethod.val: im(不) + palpable(可触摸的) → 无法触及的

words.tran: 不能触觉或感知的状态或性质

trans.tranCn: 感触不到的, 摸不到的, 难解的
trans.tranOther: impossible to touch or feel physically
